race.comment: LAWRENNY BOYS (3) led and fought on to just miss last start over 1100m at this track. Will push forward and hard to beat in a suitable race. UPHEAVAL (4) needed it on debut and then was sharply better when beaten 2.5 lengths over 1200m at this track. Has an awkward gate but won't have to improve much to feature. GEEGEES MERCEDES (8) was quickly back on track beaten 1.3L here from the speed. She's also back in trip but with the small claims is a genuine contender. OUTBUSH (1) is third-up and should be ready to show her true form. Finally draws an inside barrier and can use  it. Gets in well with the 3kg claim. ARLAUNYA (5) is ex Victoria and has been of the scene for a long while. Has trialled well enough for the new yard to deserve a betting watch.
